trend_summary: Built-up cover grows slowly through housing infill, enlarged commercial facilities and minor road widening, nudging density upward while still preserving large tree canopy and parks. Change is inward, with no significant outward sprawl.
notable_changes: Incremental housing infill along radial and peripheral streets, filling former large lots and gaps.
Commercial/ institutional complex in the northeast expands, adding new buildings and parking.
Arterial roads subtly widened and intersections re-configured, improving connectivity.
Slight tree-canopy loss in central blocks due to redevelopment, though major parks remain intact.
New or upgraded sports field/green space in the western quadrant.
